text: Propupa is an extinct genus of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the superfamily Pupilloidea. Propupa hoffeinsorum is the only species in the genus Propupa, and was described from a fossil found in Baltic amber in 2006. ==References== Category:Eocene gastropods Category:Stylommatophora Category:Baltic amber Category:Fossil taxa described in 2006
title: Propupa
